<SLUG> BC-CHURCHSHOOTING-SCHOOL-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ADMINISTRATOR ORDERS ELEMENTARY SCHOOL CLOSED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By YVETTE CRAIG 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _Fort Worth School Superintendent Thomas Tocco
has ordered Bruce Shulkey Elementary School closed Thursday because
of its proximity to Wedgwood Baptist Church, where investigators
continue probing why a gunman would turn a church sanctuary into a
killing field.
</P>
<P>
   Classes have not not been canceled elsewhere, and crisis teams
have been deployed to assist school leaders and teachers help
students cope with the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
   Police and city leaders said there will be a lot of activity at
Wedgwood Baptist, which is located at 5522 Whitman Ave. In
addition, there were unconfirmed reports of possible bomb devices
used in the crime.
</P>
<P>
   ``There is too much going on in this area, and we do not want
these young children around for obvious reasons,'' Tocco said of
the students at Bruce Shulky.
</P>
<P>
   Parents are being urged not to take their students to the
elementary school, which is across the street from the church, at
5533 Whitman Avenue. Instead, parents who are unable to provide
accommodations for their young children are being asked to take
them to one of three neighboring schools.
</P>
<P>
   School buses will be running as scheduled, Tocco said.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is clearly a tragic situation,'' Tocco said Wednesday
night. ``I think one teacher may have been killed.''
</P>
<P>
   Tocco said: ``We have gotten school counselors and psychologists
together and they will be available to help students try and
understand how to make sense of any of this.''
</P>
<P>
   A hot line has been established to assist parents. The number is
(817) 370-5850. Tocco asked parents to be patient.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
