<P>
   GERMANY-SCHROEDER-ASSESS (Berlin) _ Among recent telephone calls
to Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder was one from President Clinton who
urged the German leader to stand firm in his gathering crisis.
Political troughs may be common, but the place Schroeder finds
himself looks more like a ravine. Battered in recent state
elections, disavowed by many members of his own Social Democratic
party, Schroeder has seen his approval rating plunge to under 30
percent. By Roger Cohen.
</P>
<P>
   TIMOR-REFUGEES (Darwin, Australia) _ Refugees from East Timor
tell of horrors they fled. By Mark Landler.
</P>
