relentlessly against the Japanese yen all summer and hit a 40-month
low this week. But for all the popular fears raised by a falling
currency, the direct threat to the U.S. economy is actually quite
small. On the other hand, the threat to Japan from a stronger
currency is far more grave. By Michael M. Weinstein.
