<SLUG> BC-HKN-DUCKS-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MIGHTY DUCKS NOTES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GREG CHRISTENSEN  
 c.1999 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  ANAHEIM, Calif. _ It's one thing for a fresh-faced rookie to
catch the eye of a coach in training camp, but it's Teemu Selanne
who has impressed MightY Ducks coach Craig Hartsburg so far this
year.
</P>
<P>
   ``Teemu has had a great camp, he's been a real leader, said
Hartsburg of Selanne, who scored a league-leading 47 goals and a
team-high 107 points in 1998-99. ``I think he really wants to take
the next step ... become a winner, a leader.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a superstar, but there is more for him to give and so far
he's giving it.
</P>
<P>
   --
</P>
<P>
   Vitaly Vishnevski, 19, may represent the future of the Mighty
Ducks' defense, a physical player who has already displayed nasty
streak. Some have even compared his style to that of former Detroit
star Vladimir Konstantinov.
</P>
<P>
   Vishnevski's skills were on display in Anaheim's exhibition game
against San Jose Wednesday night, but Hartsburg said the team's No.
1 draft choice in 1998 (5th overall) will start the season at
Cincinnati of the American Hockey League.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's 19 years old and not ready, said Hartsburg when asked
why. ``He needs to develop at the right pace. He needs to play
25-30 minutes a game and that won't happen here.
</P>
<P>
   The Ducks' other highly touted youngster, 20-year old winger
Maxim Balmochnykh, will also start the year in Cincinnati.
</P>
<P>
   --
</P>
<P>
   Without Paul Kariya, Selanne, Guy Hebert and Steve Rucchin in
Wednesday's lineup there wasn't a lot to keep the fans interested
from an Anaheim point of view. But a few made do by booing the
return of Gary Suter to the Pond.
</P>
<P>
   It was Suter's first appearance in Anaheim since he knocked
Kariya out for the season on Feb. 1, 1998 with a cross check to the
jaw.
</P>
<P>
   Suter, who missed the entire '98-99 season due to a staph
infection, has yet to play against Kariya since the incident.
</P>
<P>
   --
</P>
<P>
   Defenseman Pascal Trepanier, who is coming off reconstructive
knee surgery, has yet to play in a game or scrimmage, but Hartsburg
said he is ``skating very well and could play in Monday's game
versus the Kings.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-16-99 0219EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
