<P>
   DIXIE CHICKS-EARL &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The hottest country CD is the Dixie Chicks' ``Fly,'' and the
most talked-about song on it is ``Goodbye Earl,'' a jaunty tune
that features friendship, domestic violence and murder. Pop music
critic Dave Ferman looks at the incredible response to ``Earl'' and
the reaction to it around the country _ which has been mainly
favorable. By DAVE FERMAN. Story will move in ``e'' entertainment
category &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   F I N A N C I A L &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BIZBOOKS-REVIEWS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Ray Kroc may be synonymous with McDonald's in the
United States, but in Russia, George Cohon is the man behind the
restaurant. His amazing feat in establishing the first McDonald's
restaurant in Moscow, along with the rest of Cohon's life, is
chronicled in his autobiography, ``To Russia With Fries: My Journey
From Chicago's South Side to Moscow's Red Square _ Having Fun Along
the Way'' (McClelland &AMP; Stewart, 335 pages, $21.95). Writer David
Macfarlane co-authored the book. By TERESA McUSIC. Story will move
in ``f'' financial category &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SANDERS-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ For years, in our blind and selfish arrogance, we have
sent the wrong messages to adults and teen-agers about violence,
and then feigned shock when our communities were rocked by random,
senseless, man-made calamities. We live in a state where
politicians believe that during campaigns they have to be seen with
guns as big as their smiles, shooting down some innocent critter.
It's expected. How can you get elected in Texas these days without
proclaiming your love for guns? By BOB RAY SANDERS. Story will move
in ``k'' commentary category &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   JOHNSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Something clearly needs to be done to break the
bondage of candidates to television advertising. But that's wishful
thinking. For now, doing something to curtail ``political money
laundering'' would help immensely. By CECIL JOHNSON. Story will
move in ``k'' commentary category &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
