<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STAPLES-COLUMN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PERFECT GIFTS FROM GOD COME IN ALL SHAPES, SIZES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GRACIE BONDS STAPLES 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   A friend of mine recently shared with me part of a conversation
he had with a nun.
</P>
<P>
   He told me he'd been particularly struck by her vow of poverty
and by how that allowed her a certain freedom _ from financial
woes, specifically.
</P>
<P>
   I told him that you don't have to be a nun to find freedom from
financial cares. All one needs, really, is faith that God is
all-powerful, all-knowing and means exactly what he says.
</P>
<P>
   I then rattled off a few Scriptures _ ``be anxious for nothing,
I came that they might have life and have it abundantly, lay aside
every weight'' _ related to the subject.
</P>
<P>
   He was quiet. Not sure what to make of the silence, I kept
talking. I told him that I was speaking from experience, that I've
never been without what I needed. Sometimes I have had to wait for
the things I want, but I get those things as well.
</P>
<P>
   It had been the same way growing up in Mississippi with nine
siblings and very little money.
</P>
<P>
   Now. Two things. First, this is not an attempt to discourage
anyone from becoming a nun. Second, from here on out I will refer
to my God as Christ. That does not mean I don't recognize that
there are other religions.
</P>
<P>
   But it does mean that I believe having Christ and his word
within me puts me on the road to freedom, not only in my finances
but in my will, intellect, emotions, family, job, relationships and
future, and that without him, my life would be a mess.
</P>
<P>
   The way I see it, Christ's freedom is liberation of the soul. It
can be enjoyed not just in a monastery, but behind prison walls or
in the midst of injustice.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, that's a lot harder to believe if your trust is based
totally on sight and circumstances.
</P>
<P>
   But as is often the case when I share my faith with someone, God
will test my words to see _ or rather for me to see _ if I'm simply
giving lip service or if I really mean what I say.
</P>
<P>
   Enter the child in my life who's always teaching me something:
Jamila.
</P>
<P>
   We were on our way to a piano recital shortly after I spouted
off with my friend. Jamila and Asha were in the back seat talking
about all the things that make our family rich.
</P>
<P>
   Being the good mommy that I am, I piped up to share with my
little darlings the real deal. In my most soothing voice _ I didn't
want them to go into convulsions _ I said, ``Hey guys, we're not
rich.''
</P>
<P>
   In disbelief, Jamila shot back, ``Mama, H-E-L-L-O!''
</P>
<P>
   As in, how stupid can you be, woman?
</P>
<P>
   I craned my neck to look back at her, and as is normally the
case, she's waving her little hands to help drive home her point,
to school her poor mother.
</P>
<P>
   ``I mean God,'' she said. ``Rich in God.''
</P>
<P>
   Well, I wanted to disappear. I was so embarrassed, I thought if
I ever got pregnant again _ which isn't likely _ but if by some
miracle I did, I will never again read Scripture aloud to my fetus.
</P>
<P>
   I'm convinced that this is why this child is so spiritually
minded.
</P>
<P>
   In any case, I was immediately reminded of my conversation with
my friend and all my talk about blessings and peace of mind,
Christ's gifts to those who trust in him.
</P>
<P>
   And so I had to ask myself, ``Do I really believe all good and
perfect gifts come from God, that he will supply all of my needs,
or was I simply paying him lip service?''
</P>
<P>
   I remembered this from Matthew 15:8 _ ``This people draweth nigh
unto me with their mouth, and honoreth me with their lips, but
their heart is far away from me.''
</P>
<P>
   God has made many wonderful promises toward us. It's nice to be
able to repeat them, but how many of them do we really believe?
</P>
<P>
   Better yet, how often do we live like it?
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
