   FBC-LINEMEN (Austin, Texas) _ When Texas won the national
championship in college football in 1969, the Longhorns' offensive
line averaged 213 pounds. Thirty years later, the typical offensive
lineman weighs more than 100 pounds above that. By NEIL HOHLFELD
</P>
<P>
   FBN-ANDERSON (Dallas) _ Jamal Anderson emerged as one of the
premier running backs in the NFL last season, rushing for more than
1,800 yards and helping lead the Atlanta Falcons to their first
Super Bowl. After a highly publicized contract holdout this summer,
Anderson is back and ready to show his best against the Dallas
Cowboys next week in a nationally televised Monday night game. By
JODY GOLDSTEIN.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ The flap over allowing divorced
women or those who have had an abortion to enter the Miss America
contest is not really about changing the feminine ``ideal.'' It is
really about subjecting what is nothing but a beauty pageant to the
impact of religious politics. Contest officials should simply copy
the military's ``don't ask, don't tell'' stand on gays. The sex
life of the contestants is nobody's business anyway. By MARIANNE
MEANS.
</P>
