<P>
   PROTEST-VIEQUES (Washington) _ The U.S. Navy wants federal law
officers to arrest three dozen protesters camped out on a Navy
bombing range on the Puerto Rican island of Vieques. The
demonstrators are trying to prevent resumption of Navy and Marine
target practice there. But the Puerto Rico governor objects to any
arrests, the U.S. attorney there refuses to order them and some New
York City Council members say they'll join the protesters on
Vieques. By STEWART M. POWELL.
