near Cape Fear, N.C., with 110 mph winds, flooding the Carolina
coasts with more than a foot of rain as tens of thousands of people
huddled in shelters. At least seven deaths are blamed on the storm.
More than 480,000 people customers in the Carolinas and Virginia
have lost power. Flooding and power failures combined to shut down
