It wasn't always clear from what. Sure, Hurricane Floyd was
supposed to roar into town Thursday and topple buildings and
catapult buses over the World Trade Center _ but where was it? The
day the hurricane was due was very much a day of pointed contrasts
in the metropolitan area, with portions of the area being pounded,
while the city itself was tricked by a non-event. By N.R.
