<HEADLINE>
SECOND COMPLAINT AGAINST STATE SEN. BROWN WILL NOT BE PURSUED,
POLICE SAY 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By STEVE OLAFSON 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAKE JACKSON, Texas _ Police won't pursue an investigation into
a second complaint that state Sen. J.E. ``Buster'' Brown made
unwanted sexual advances on a woman, officials said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The second complaint, made by an Alvin woman, alleged the
senator grabbed her and tried to kiss her as she was leaving his
Lake Jackson office after consulting him about a legal matter, said
Police Chief Paul Hromadka.
</P>
<P>
   Because the alleged incident occurred about six months past the
two-year statute of limitations for misdemeanor assault cases,
police will not look any further into the allegation, Hromadka
said.
</P>
<P>
   The Alvin woman notified Lake Jackson police Monday after
reading news coverage of the first complaint made against Brown by
Tiffany Black, a former employee of the senator's, Hromadka said.
</P>
<P>
   The Alvin woman, interviewed Wednesday night by police, notified
authorities about what happened to her to support the allegations
made by Black, a 20-year-old college student, said Hromadka.
</P>
<P>
   The woman did not want to pursue criminal charges for what she
said happened to her, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Police did not interview Brown, 57, about the alleged second
incident.
</P>
<P>
   Brown, the ranking Republican in the Texas Senate, did not
return a call for comment.
</P>
<P>
   He apologized Wednesday to Black, a Brazosport College student
who quit her job with the senator on Sept. 2 after she told police
he tried to kiss her and touched her breasts and buttocks at his
Lake Jackson office.
</P>
<P>
   Brown's written apology, in which he acknowledged making
unwanted sexual advances toward Black, stated he will seek ``any
necessary corrective measures, including counseling.``
</P>
<P>
   Lake Jackson is about 55 miles south of downtown Houston. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
