<P>
   ERXLEBEN _ AUSTIN _ Attorneys representing as many as 300
investors are expected to file a lawsuit Thursday against the law
firms and accountants that advised Austin Forex, Russell Erxleben's
ill-fated, foreign-currency trading firm. It's been almost a year
to the day that Austin Forex closed its doors, leaving scores of
investors financially devastated. As Erxleben, who claims he's
broke, slowly twists, waiting to see if he'll be indicted for his
role in the debacle, investors are now searching for elsewhere for
deep pockets. (Pletz, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
