<P>
   JOEMURRAY-COLUMN _ WASHINGTON _ It was Sunday morning in our
nation's capital, and I was spending it as I have countless Sunday
mornings, boy and man, occupying a pew at the First Baptist Church.
The first time for me at this, the First Baptist of Washington,
D.C., but I felt right at home. (Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ The curious nature of municipal
politics keeps Austin's enemies stocked with eye-rolling anecdotes
they gleefully relay to an audience that can't get enough of them.
What's keeping them in yucks lately is the microscopic analysis of
the water deal offered by the Lower Colorado River Authority. While
Austinites insist on worshiping at the altar of process,
legislators and others around the state are once again shaking
their heads. (Arnold Garcia is editorial page editor of the Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MCNEELY-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ The race to be the next
lieutenant governor is on _ despite an effort by one of the
Senate's most respected members to keep it from happening.
(McNeely, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
