   &QL; 
FORBES (Tucson, Ariz.) - Steve Forbes won big in the Arizona
presidential primary in 1996, and now he wants to do it again. On
Thursday he opens his campaign here in a three-day blitz that
promises to be the longest and most expensive entry into Arizona of
any of the campaigns so far, with speeches and appearances in
Tucson and Phoenix. The effort comes at time when Forbes campaign
is dragging in the polls
</P>
