contest is not really about changing the feminine ``ideal.'' It is
really about subjecting what is nothing but a beauty pageant to the
impact of religious politics. Contest officials should simply copy
the military's ``don't ask, don't tell'' stand on gays. The sex
life of the contestants is nobody's business anyway. By MARIANNE
MEANS.
