</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Opera unveils casts, directors for 2000 season
 &HT;    By Judith Green
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Atlanta Opera has announced casts and directors for the operas
of its 2000 season. All shows are at the Fox Theatre. Season
tickets are $58-$476 at 404-881-8885.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Rigoletto'' (April 6-9). Verdi's tragedy of a hunchbacked
jester and his vulnerable daughter, undone by a greedy and sensual
aristocrat. With baritone Thomas Potter in the title role, tenor
Eduardo Villa (``La Boheme'') as the Duke of Mantua, soprano Paula
Delligatti (``Madama Butterfly,'' 1996) as Gilda. Guest conductor:
John Balme of Lake George Opera Festival. (Artistic director
William Fred Scott will be conducting Bizet's ``The Pearl Fishers''
at Sarasota Opera in Florida.) Stage director: Christopher
Mattaliano.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Cosi fan tutte'' (June 8-11). Mozart's comedy about the
amorous unpredictability of women. With three returnees from ``The
Capulets and the Montagues'': soprano Brenda Harris and mezzo
Delores Ziegler as Fiordiligi and Dorabella, bass Philip Cokorinos
as Don Alfonso. Director: Nicolette Molnar. New production designed
by Peter Dean Beck.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Lucia di Lammermoor'' (Sept. 14-17). Gaetano Donizetti's bel
canto tragedy of a noblewoman forced into a political marriage.
With soprano Sally Wolf in the title role; Mexican tenor Jorge
Lopez-Yanez as Edgardo. Director: Ken Cazan.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Turandot'' (Oct. 26-29). Puccini's fantasy about an icy
Chinese princess who refuses to marry any suitor who cannot answer
three riddles. With Metropolitan Opera soprano Martile Rowland in
the title role, Villa as Calaf, Kelley Nassief (``La Boheme'') as
Liu. Director: Dijan Miladinovic. New production designed by Beck.
</P>
<P>
   _ Judith Green writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
