<HEADLINE>
ERRONEOUS REPORT OF TEEN'S SHOOTING SHAKES FAMILY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Matt Parr's family spent most of Thursday
giving friends the good news that he was fine after the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram erroneously reported that the teen had been hurt in
Wednesday's church shooting rampage.
</P>
<P>
   The phone started ringing about 5 a.m. as friends read the
newspaper and saw Matt Parr's name and picture in a partial list of
seven slain victims and seven wounded.
</P>
<P>
   Kurt Parr said his wife assured the first caller that her
16-year-old son was safely in bed. But when she hung up the phone,
she went to check on the teen just to make sure, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Once the calls began, ``there was just a constant stream,'' Parr
said.
</P>
<P>
   The 16-year-old had little reaction, his dad said, because he
was far more troubled by the tragedy that hurt so many people he
knew, including his aunt, who was wounded.
</P>
<P>
   Kurt Parr said he is astounded that his son's name, and
particularly his picture, could appear in the newspaper without the
information being verified.
</P>
<P>
   In this case, neither law enforcement nor hospital officials
were releasing names, so verifying identies became an arduous task.
Parr's name was added to a list of victims, all of which were to be
confirmed.
</P>
<P>
   However, in the chaos of trying to sift through dozens of
reports _ some true, some not _ Parr's name was overlooked and not
verified.
</P>
<P>
   ``Whether it's this story or any other, accuracy is always the
most important aspect of our work,'' Fort Worth Star-Telegram
Managing Editor Kathy Vetter said. ``In this case, the scene at the
church was chaotic and the pace in the newsroom hectic. That does
not excuse the unneccesary trouble, and the needless worry, we
caused Matt Parr's friends and family.''
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
