<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following sports
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sept. 17 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Eddie Ibardolasa at (818) 713-3602. 
 
 
BOX-ARUM (Las Vegas) _ Promoter Bob Arum, who has worked with
fighters like Marvin Hagler and Sugar Ray Leonard, said his latest
creation _ Oscar De La Hoya _ is his masterpiece. How did it
happen? 
By Michael Rosenthal. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BOX-TYSON (Las Vegas) _ Mike Tyson, four months out of prison and
preparing for his comeback fight against Orlin Norris here on Oct.
23, spreads around the blame for his troubles. Among the cultprits:
the justice system, the media, his colleagues _ himself. 
By Michael Rosenthal. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BOX-BOXNOTES (Las Vegas) _ Boxing notebook. 
By Michael Rosenthal. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-BROWN (Los Angeles) _ Kevin Brown, the $110 million man, while
not exactly the positive clubhouse influence as advertised, has
done exactly what the Los Angeles Dodgers signed him for: pitched a
lot of innings, and pitched well. As the season winds down, he is
still in pursuit of a 20-win year with four starts left. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
FBC-USC (Wolf) _ Feature on the USC football team's defense. It was
supposed to be the weak link of this club, but it's proven to be
better and faster than anyone anticipated. 
By Scott Wolf. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
