RAC-HORSE-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ J.C. Gonzalez, killed last week at
Fairplex Park, was the first pupil of the Frank Garza Jockey School
in Newbury Park to make it as a professional race-rider. Garza
considered Gonzalez part of his family and said he's ``devastated''
by his death. 
