-- James Becker, right, and Stephen Raymond, co-founders of the PHT
Corp., use a PlexxNet Patient LogPad at their office earlier this
week. As part of its ordeal to get permission to market its drug to
treat rheumatoid arthritis, Celebrex, G.D. Searle at one point sent
an 18-wheel truck to the US Food and Drug Administration, loaded
with pallets of paper records on 14,000 people who had participated
in 61 clinical trials over a five-year period. The logpad enables
patients to enter their data electronically eliminating the
paperwork. (Pam Berry/Boston Globe Photo)
