<SLUG> BC-FBN-FALCONS-NOTES17-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Reeves recalls `Opie' Gailey
 &HT;    By Matt Winkeljohn
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Falcons coach Dan Reeves had Cowboys coach Chan Gailey
on his staff in Denver from 1985-90, and both are natives of
Americus. Reeves even coached Gailey in youth baseball, and has
described him as ``one of those kids you kind of fall in love with
the first time you meet them. He was always there every day with a
smile on his face.''
</P>
<P>
   Reeves even compared the young Gailey to ``Opie,'' the
red-haired boy on the old ``Andy Griffith Show'' set in Mayberry,
N.C.
</P>
<P>
   On a teleconference Thursday, Gailey was asked the size of
Americus, in southwest Georgia.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is a little bit bigger than Mayberry,'' Gailey said.
</P>
<P>
   The next question was, ``Is Mayberry a neighboring community?''
</P>
<P>
   Gailey didn't miss a beat: ``No, Mayberry is where Andy Griffith
lived.''
</P>
<P>
   Injury update
</P>
<P>
   Quarterback Chris Chandler (strained right hamstring) was joined
Thursday in the ``doubtful'' category on the injury report by
cornerback Michael Booker (partially torn quadriceps muscle) and
defensive tackle Ben Huff (sprained foot). Wide receiver Tim Dwight
(strained right hamstring) returned to practice, and was upgraded
from doubtful to questionable. ... The Cowboys' injury report is
unchanged: Tight end Mike Lucky (foot) and cornerback Kevin Smith
(back) are out; cornerback Deion Sanders (toe) is doubtful; tight
end David LaFleur (ankle), wide receiver Jeff Ogden (thigh) and
strong safety Darren Woodson (biceps) are probable.
</P>
<P>
   Facility update
</P>
<P>
   The deadline for deciding on the future location of Falcons
headquarters _ whether to stay in Suwanee and expand, or move
northeast to Hall County _ keeps getting pushed back. Actually,
there is no deadline.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't see a decision happening this week,'' said Falcons
vice president of corporate development Tommy Nobis.
</P>
<P>
   ``To say we want to be there in the middle of next August, or
next September ... that is not the priority anymore. The priority
is to get the land, and the cost, and then talk about ... dates we
could get into it.''
</P>
<P>
   Fast facts
</P>
<P>
   Reeves said if Dwight can't play, running back Byron Hanspard,
who returned two kickoffs for touchdowns as a rookie in 1997,
probably would return kickoffs in his place. Wide receiver Ronnie
Harris probably would return punts. ... The Falcons are 5-15 on
Monday nights, losing eight straight and 11 of 12. ... A call by
the Falcons' front office to the NFL to seek an interpretation of
the pass interference call against cornerback Ray Buchanan when he
was defending Minnesota's Randy Moss was fruitless. The bottom
line: Calls like that usually are left entirely up to the
official's interpretation.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
