than they have been in more than two decades, a new opinion poll
shows. In its annual survey to determine ``the mood of the public
in respect to its sense of economic well-being,'' the San
Francisco-based Field Institute found that 70 percent of
Californians think the economy is going through `'good times.'' By
Arthur M. Louis
