<SLUG> BC-NYTIMES-APPOINT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CO. AND INTERNET UNIT APPOINT EXECUTIVES 
</HEADLINE>
  (bl) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The New York Times Co. has announced the appointment
of two corporate executives. In addition, the company's Internet
business unit has appointed a chief financial officer.
</P>
<P>
   James C. Lessersohn, formerly vice president for corporate
planning, has been named vice president and treasurer of the
company. Ann S. Kraus, formerly director of compensation, has been
named vice president for compensation and benefits. Ellen Taus,
treasurer and vice president, will become chief financial officer
of the Internet business unit, Times Company Digital.
</P>
<P>
   Lessersohn, 44, who succeeds Ms. Taus, joined the Times company
as a project manager in 1987. He was named a vice president for
corporate planning in 1997. Ms. Kraus, 49, joined the company as
director of compensation in 1997. She was previously director for
compensation of Prudential Insurance Co.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Taus, 41, joined the company as an assistant treasurer in
1996. She had previously worked for R.H. Macy, the American Museum
of the Moving Image, TW Services and New York and Foreign
Securities.
</P>
<P>
   Times Company Digital operates nearly 50 Web sites, including
the sites of The New York Times and The Boston Globe, nytoday.com,
winetoday.com and golfdigest.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
